quran[64]{c,v,t}:
  84,1,When the sky splits
  84,2,and it listens to its Master and it is required (to listen)
  84,3,and when the earth is stretched
  84,4,and throws out what is inside of it and becomes empty
  84,5,and it listens to its Master and it is required (to listen)
  84,6,"Human being, indeed you are a hard worker toward your Master, working hard, and you meet Him"
  84,7,As for anyone who is given his book to his right hand
  84,8,"then he is called to account, an easy account"
  84,9,and he returns happily to his family
  84,10,But anyone who is given his book from behind his back
  84,11,Then he will call for destruction (and his death)
  84,12,while he enters (and burns in) the burning fire
  84,13,Indeed he was happy among his family
  84,14,Indeed he thought that he would never return
  84,15,"Yes, his Master was indeed watching him"
  84,16,So I swear by the sunset glow
  84,17,and the night and what it collects
  84,18,and the moon when it is full
  84,19,that you shall move on from state after state
  84,20,So what is with them that they do not believe
  84,21,"and when the Quran is read to them, they do not show humbleness"
  84,22,"No, but those who disbelieved deny"
  84,23,and God knows better what they hold (inside them)
  84,24,So give them the news of a painful punishment
  84,25,"except those who believed and did good works, as they have an unending reward"
  85,1,By the sky having the constellations
  85,2,and by the promised day
  85,3,and by a witness and a witnessed
  85,4,Damn the directors of the fire pit
  85,5,the fire having (plenty of) the fuel
  85,6,when they sat around it
  85,7,and they were witnesses over what they did to the believers
  85,8,"And they only took revenge from them for believing in God the powerful, the praiseworthy"
  85,9,"The One that the rule of the skies and the earth belongs to Him, and God is a witness over everything"
  85,10,"Indeed those who persecuted (and tortured) the believing men and the believing women and did not repent, punishment of hell is for them and the burning punishment is for them"
  85,11,"Indeed those who believed and did good works, for them are gardens which rivers flow through them. That is the great victory"
  85,12,Indeed your Master’s assault is severe
  85,13,Indeed He initiates and repeats (the creation)
  85,14,"and He is the forgiving, the most friendly"
  85,15,owner of the glorious throne
  85,16,doer of what He wants
  85,17,Did the story of the armies come to you
  85,18,Pharaoh and the Thamud
  85,19,But those who disbelieved are in a denial
  85,20,And God is surrounding over and above them
  85,21,This is a glorious Quran
  85,22,in a guarded (and protected) tablet
  86,1,By the sky and the night-comer (the evening star)
  86,2,And do you know what the evening star is
  86,3,It is the sharp bright star
  86,4,Indeed every person has a guardian (watching) over him
  86,5,So the human being should look at what he is created from
  86,6,He is created from an ejected fluid
  86,7,coming out from between the backbone and the ribs
  86,8,Indeed He is capable of his return
  86,9,a day that the secrets are disclosed
  86,10,then he has no power and no helper
  86,11,And by the sky that has the returning (rain clouds)
  86,12,and by the earth having the crack (for sprouting)
  86,13,indeed it (Quran) is a decisive word
  86,14,and it is not a joke
  86,15,Indeed they plot a plot
  86,16,and I plan a plan
  86,17,"So give the disbelievers time, give them time without rushing"